# Experiments Queue

Autoresearch reads this file to build task queue. Each task is an independent optimization experiment. Edit sections to queue new tasks or modify existing ones.

## Task 1: Tile Subdivision Optimization

**Component:** tile_subdiv (Phase 3)

**Goal:** Reduce shader pass latency by optimizing tile marker distribution.

**Changes:**
- Cache tile split candidates to avoid redundant marker writes
- Reduce warp instruction divergence in marker comparison pass
- Unroll inner loop by 2x with early-exit heuristic

**Baseline Metrics:**
```
tile_subdiv_pass_ms: 2.3 @ 1920x1080, zoom 0.1x
Instructions per marker: 45 avg
Register pressure: 78%
```

**Target:**
- < 2.0ms (13% improvement)
- Register pressure: < 70%

**Success Criteria:**
- Code compiles without warnings (clippy -D)
- All existing tests pass
- Perf improvement > 1% (measurement > noise floor)
- Memory footprint ± 2%

