## Task 3: Tet Mesh Compression

**Component:** tet_propagation (Phase 1-2)

**Goal:** Reduce GPU heap memory footprint and improve cache locality.

**Changes:**
- Pack face adjacency into 16-bit indices (was 32-bit)
- Use packed edge codes to avoid separate adjacency texture
- Compact implicit tet storage via BFS wavefront encoding

**Baseline Metrics:**
```
gpu_heap_mb: 512 (1M tets @ Phase 6 LOD)
Face adjacency texture: 256 MB
Working set per frame: 384 MB
```

**Target:**
- < 384 MB total (25% reduction)
- No perf regression (cached reads faster due to density)

**Success Criteria:**
- GPU heap < 384 MB
- Benchmark latency ± 3%
- Phase 5+ subdivision still correct

